{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":865,"text":"I would like to invite you"},{"time":2611,"text":"to come along on a visit"},{"time":4341,"text":"to a dark continent."},{"time":6399,"text":"It is the continent hidden"},{"time":8037,"text":"under the surface of the earth."},{"time":10113,"text":"It is largely unexplored,"},{"time":12430,"text":"poorly understood,\nand the stuff of legends."},{"time":15137,"text":"But it is made also of dramatic landscapes"},{"time":17999,"text":"like this huge underground chamber,"},{"time":20518,"text":"and it is rich with surprising\nbiological and mineralogical worlds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26149,"text":"Thanks to the efforts of intrepid voyagers\nin the last three centuries --"},{"time":30999,"text":"actually, we know also thanks\nto satellite technology, of course --"},{"time":34857,"text":"we know almost every single square meter\nof our planet's surface."},{"time":39085,"text":"However, we know still very little\nabout what is hidden inside the earth."},{"time":44050,"text":"Because a cave landscape,\nlike this deep shaft in Italy, is hidden,"},{"time":49999,"text":"the potential of cave exploration --\nthe geographical dimension --"},{"time":53377,"text":"is poorly understood and unappreciated."},{"time":55769,"text":"Because we are creatures\nliving on the surface,"},{"time":58828,"text":"our perception of the inner\nside of the planet"},{"time":62999,"text":"is in some ways skewed,"},{"time":64987,"text":"as is that of the depth of the oceans"},{"time":67463,"text":"or of the upper atmosphere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71094,"text":"However, since systematic cave exploration\nstarted about one century ago,"},{"time":78076,"text":"we know actually that caves exist\nin every continent of the world."},{"time":82471,"text":"A single cave system,\nlike Mammoth Cave, which is in Kentucky,"},{"time":86539,"text":"can be as long\nas more than 600 kilometers."},{"time":91270,"text":"And an abyss like Krubera Voronya,\nwhich is in the Caucasus region,"},{"time":95401,"text":"actually the deepest cave\nexplored in the world,"},{"time":98203,"text":"can go as far as more than 2,000\nmeters below the surface."},{"time":102548,"text":"That means a journey of weeks\nfor a cave explorer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107545,"text":"Caves form in karstic regions."},{"time":110795,"text":"So karstic regions are areas of the world"},{"time":113999,"text":"where the infiltrating water\nalong cracks, fractures,"},{"time":117513,"text":"can easily dissolve soluble lithologies,"},{"time":121497,"text":"forming a drainage system\nof tunnels, conduits --"},{"time":124301,"text":"a three-dimensional network, actually."},{"time":126804,"text":"Karstic regions cover almost 20 percent\nof the continents' surface,"},{"time":132707,"text":"and we know actually that speleologists\nin the last 50 years"},{"time":137855,"text":"have explored roughly 30,000 kilometers\nof cave passages around the world,"},{"time":143543,"text":"which is a big number."},{"time":144935,"text":"But geologists have estimated\nthat what is still missing,"},{"time":149458,"text":"to be discovered and mapped,"},{"time":151712,"text":"is something around 10 million kilometers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155287,"text":"That means that for each meter\nof a cave that we already know,"},{"time":158601,"text":"that we have explored,"},{"time":160158,"text":"there are still some tens of kilometers\nof undiscovered passages."},{"time":165576,"text":"That means that this is really\nan endless continent,"},{"time":168515,"text":"and we will never be able\nto explore it completely."},{"time":172597,"text":"And this estimation is made\nwithout considering other types of caves,"},{"time":176117,"text":"like, for example, inside glaciers\nor even volcanic caves,"},{"time":180580,"text":"which are not karstic,\nbut are formed by lava flows."},{"time":184136,"text":"And if we have a look at other planets\nlike, for example, Mars,"},{"time":189816,"text":"you will see that this characteristic"},{"time":191690,"text":"is not so specific of our home planet."},{"time":195623,"text":"However, I will show to you now\nthat we do not need to go to Mars"},{"time":199999,"text":"to explore alien worlds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203750,"text":"I'm a speleologist, that means\na cave explorer."},{"time":207714,"text":"And I started with this passion\nwhen I was really young"},{"time":211646,"text":"in the mountains not far\nfrom my hometown in North Italy,"},{"time":215731,"text":"in the karstic regions of the Alps\nand the Dolomites."},{"time":219252,"text":"But soon, the quest for exploration\nbrought me to the farthest corner"},{"time":223117,"text":"of the planet, searching\nfor new potential entrances"},{"time":225870,"text":"of this undiscovered continent."},{"time":228578,"text":"And in 2009, I had the opportunity\nto visit the tepui table mountains,"},{"time":233663,"text":"which are in the Orinoco\nand Amazon basins."},{"time":236683,"text":"These massifs enchanted me\nfrom the first time I saw them."},{"time":241259,"text":"They are surrounded by vertical,\nvertiginous rock walls"},{"time":244650,"text":"with silvery waterfalls\nthat are lost in the forest."},{"time":248145,"text":"They really inspired in me\na sense of wilderness,"},{"time":251501,"text":"with a soul older than millions\nand millions of years."},{"time":255480,"text":"And this dramatic landscape\ninspired among other things"},{"time":259415,"text":"also Conan Doyle's\n\"The Lost World\" novel in 1912."},{"time":263999,"text":"And they are, really, a lost world."},{"time":269001,"text":"Scientists consider those mountains\nas islands in time,"},{"time":274310,"text":"being separated\nfrom the surrounding lowlands"},{"time":276972,"text":"since tens of millions of years ago."},{"time":279680,"text":"They are surrounded\nby up to 1,000-meter-high walls,"},{"time":283605,"text":"resembling a fortress,\nimpregnable by humans."},{"time":286761,"text":"And, in fact, only a few\nof these mountains have been climbed"},{"time":289999,"text":"and explored on their top."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292740,"text":"These mountains contain also\na scientific paradox:"},{"time":295633,"text":"They are made by quartz,"},{"time":297717,"text":"which is a very common mineral\non the earth's crust,"},{"time":300908,"text":"and the rock made up by quartz\nis called quartzite,"},{"time":305310,"text":"and quartzite is one of the hardest\nand least soluble minerals on earth."},{"time":310642,"text":"So we do not expect at all\nto find a cave there."},{"time":314057,"text":"Despite this, in the last 10 years,\nspeleologists from Italy,"},{"time":318999,"text":"Slovakia, Czech Republic,\nand, of course, Venezuela and Brazil,"},{"time":322828,"text":"have explored several caves in this area."},{"time":325831,"text":"So how can it be possible?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":328342,"text":"To understand this contradiction,\nwe have to consider the time factor,"},{"time":332427,"text":"because the history of the tepuis\nis extremely long,"},{"time":335754,"text":"starting about 1.6 billion years ago\nwith the formation of the rock,"},{"time":340435,"text":"and then evolving with the uplift\nof the region 150 million years ago,"},{"time":346999,"text":"after the disruption\nof the Pangaea supercontinent"},{"time":349999,"text":"and the opening of the Atlantic Ocean."},{"time":352376,"text":"So you can imagine that the water had tens\nor even hundreds of millions of years"},{"time":358710,"text":"to sculpt the strangest forms\non the tepuis' surfaces,"},{"time":362792,"text":"but also to open the fractures\nand form stone cities, rock cities,"},{"time":368830,"text":"fields of towers which are characterized\nin the famous landscape of the tepuis."},{"time":374375,"text":"But nobody could have imagined"},{"time":375843,"text":"what was happening inside a mountain\nin so long a time frame."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380603,"text":"And so I was focusing in 2010\non one of those massifs,"},{"time":385104,"text":"the Auyán-tepui, which is very famous\nbecause it hosts Angel Falls,"},{"time":388979,"text":"which is the highest\nwaterfall in the world --"},{"time":391592,"text":"about 979 meters of vertical drop."},{"time":395675,"text":"And I was searching for hints\nof the existence of cave systems"},{"time":400585,"text":"through satellite images,"},{"time":402477,"text":"and finally we identified an area\nof collapses of the surface --"},{"time":407191,"text":"so, big boulders, rock piles --"},{"time":409461,"text":"and that means that there\nwas a void below."},{"time":412796,"text":"It was a clear indication that there\nwas something inside the mountain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416769,"text":"So we did several attempts\nto reach this area,"},{"time":421639,"text":"by land and with a helicopter,"},{"time":423425,"text":"but it was really difficult\nbecause -- you have to imagine"},{"time":426999,"text":"that these mountains are covered\nby clouds most of the year, by fog."},{"time":431402,"text":"There are strong winds,"},{"time":432799,"text":"and there are almost 4,000 millimeters\nof rainfall per year,"},{"time":437405,"text":"so it's really, really difficult\nto find good conditions."},{"time":440691,"text":"And only in 2013 we finally\nlanded on the spot"},{"time":445498,"text":"and we started\nthe exploration of the cave."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448723,"text":"The cave is huge."},{"time":450664,"text":"It's a huge network under the surface\nof the tepui plateau,"},{"time":454515,"text":"and in only ten days of expedition,"},{"time":458233,"text":"we explored more than 20 kilometers\nof cave passages."},{"time":462380,"text":"And it's a huge network\nof underground rivers,"},{"time":467801,"text":"channels, big rooms,\nextremely deep shafts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":472999,"text":"So it's really an incredible place."},{"time":476047,"text":"And we named it Imawarì Yeuta."},{"time":478612,"text":"That means, in the Pemón indigenous\nlanguage, \"The House of the Gods.\""},{"time":484897,"text":"You have to imagine that indigenous people\nhave never been there."},{"time":488703,"text":"It was impossible for them\nto reach this area."},{"time":492232,"text":"However, there were legends\nabout the existence"},{"time":494462,"text":"of a cave in the mountain."},{"time":496513,"text":"So when we started the exploration,"},{"time":498307,"text":"we had to explore with a great respect,"},{"time":500561,"text":"both because of the religious beliefs\nof the indigenous people,"},{"time":504146,"text":"but also because\nit was really a sacred place,"},{"time":506535,"text":"because no human had entered there before."},{"time":509894,"text":"So we had to use special protocols"},{"time":511721,"text":"to not contaminate the environment\nwith our presence,"},{"time":514534,"text":"and we tried also to share\nwith the community,"},{"time":516733,"text":"with the indigenous community,\nour discoveries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519430,"text":"And the caves represent, really,\na snapshot of the past."},{"time":524503,"text":"The time needed for their formation"},{"time":527239,"text":"could be as long as 50 or even\n100 million years,"},{"time":532187,"text":"which makes them possibly the oldest caves\nthat we can explore on earth."},{"time":538921,"text":"What you can find there\nis really evidence of a lost world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545301,"text":"When you enter a quartzite cave,"},{"time":547312,"text":"you have to completely forget\nwhat you know about caves --"},{"time":550784,"text":"classic limestone caves\nor the touristic caves"},{"time":553805,"text":"that you can visit\nin several places in the world."},{"time":556186,"text":"Because what seems\na simple stalactite here"},{"time":559135,"text":"is not made by calcium carbonate,\nbut is made by opal,"},{"time":564244,"text":"and one of those stalactites can require\ntens of millions of years to be formed."},{"time":570685,"text":"But you can find even stranger forms,\nlike these mushrooms of silica"},{"time":574786,"text":"growing on a boulder."},{"time":576884,"text":"And you can imagine our talks\nwhen we were exploring the cave."},{"time":580694,"text":"We were the first entering\nand discovering those unknown things,"},{"time":585711,"text":"things like those monster eggs."},{"time":588573,"text":"And we were a bit scared\nbecause it was all a discovery,"},{"time":592993,"text":"and we didn't want to find a dinosaur."},{"time":595100,"text":"We didn't find a dinosaur."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596628,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":598249,"text":"Anyway, actually, we know\nthat this kind of formation,"},{"time":601570,"text":"after several studies,"},{"time":604127,"text":"we know that these kinds of formations\nare living organisms."},{"time":607376,"text":"They are bacterial colonies using silica\nto build mineral structures"},{"time":612834,"text":"resembling stromatolites."},{"time":614788,"text":"Stromatolites are some of the oldest\nforms of life that we can find on earth."},{"time":619333,"text":"And here in the tepuis,"},{"time":621160,"text":"the interesting thing is that these\nbacteria colonies have evolved"},{"time":625867,"text":"in complete isolation\nfrom the external surface,"},{"time":630120,"text":"and without being in contact with humans."},{"time":632768,"text":"They have never been\nin contact with humans."},{"time":635389,"text":"So the implications\nfor science are enormous,"},{"time":638480,"text":"because here you could find,\nfor example, microbes"},{"time":642506,"text":"that could be useful to resolve\ndiseases in medicine,"},{"time":647482,"text":"or you could find even a new kind\nof material with unknown properties."},{"time":651442,"text":"And, in fact, we discovered in the cave\na new mineral structure for science,"},{"time":655525,"text":"which is rossiantonite,\na phosphate-sulfate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":659606,"text":"So whatever you find in the cave,\neven a small cricket,"},{"time":664344,"text":"has evolved in the dark\nin complete isolation."},{"time":668336,"text":"And, really, everything that you can feel\nin the cave are real connections"},{"time":672613,"text":"between the biological\nand the mineralogical world."},{"time":676544,"text":"So as we explore this dark continent"},{"time":682384,"text":"and discover its mineralogical\nand biological diversity and uniqueness,"},{"time":688812,"text":"we will find probably clues\nabout the origin of life on our planet"},{"time":693205,"text":"and on the relationship\nand evolution of life"},{"time":696206,"text":"in relationship with the mineral world."},{"time":699216,"text":"What seems only a dark, empty environment"},{"time":703182,"text":"could be in reality a chest of wonders"},{"time":705999,"text":"full of useful information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710102,"text":"With a team of Italian, Venezuelan\nand Brazilian speleologists,"},{"time":713999,"text":"which is called La Venta Teraphosa,"},{"time":717214,"text":"we will be back soon to Latin America,"},{"time":719306,"text":"because we want to explore other tepuis\nin the farthest areas of the Amazon."},{"time":724778,"text":"There are still very unknown mountains,"},{"time":727822,"text":"like Marahuaca, which is almost\n3,000 meters high above sea level,"},{"time":732540,"text":"or Aracà, which is in the upper region\nof Rio Negro in Brazil."},{"time":736663,"text":"And we suppose that we could find there\neven bigger cave systems,"},{"time":741606,"text":"and each one with its own\nundiscovered world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746636,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747834,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":753312,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Thank you, Francesco.\nGive me that to start so we don't forget."},{"time":757073,"text":"Francesco, you said we don't need\nto go to Mars to find alien life,"},{"time":760935,"text":"and indeed, last time we spoke,\nyou were in Sardinia"},{"time":763884,"text":"and you were training European astronauts."},{"time":766151,"text":"So what do you, a speleologist,\ntell and teach to the astronauts?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":769649,"text":"Francesco Sauro: Yeah, we are --\nit's a program of training"},{"time":772456,"text":"for not only European, but also NASA,\nRoskosmos, JAXA astronauts, in a cave."},{"time":777381,"text":"So they stay in a cave\nfor about one week in isolation."},{"time":780933,"text":"They have to work together\nin a real, real dangerous environment,"},{"time":784837,"text":"and it's a real alien environment for them\nbecause it's unusual."},{"time":788671,"text":"It's always dark. They have to do science.\nThey have a lot of tasks."},{"time":792999,"text":"And it's very similar to a journey to Mars"},{"time":795555,"text":"or the International Space Station."}]},{"cues":[{"time":797251,"text":"BG: In principle.\nFS: Yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":798534,"text":"BG: I want to go back\nto one of the pictures"},{"time":800635,"text":"that was in your slide show,"},{"time":802492,"text":"and it's just representative\nof the other photos --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":804905,"text":"Weren't those photos amazing? Yeah?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":807227,"text":"Audience: Yeah!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":808409,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":812169,"text":"FS: I have to thank the photographers\nfrom the team La Venta,"},{"time":815319,"text":"because all of those photos\nare from the photographers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":819116,"text":"BG: You bring, actually, photographers\nwith you in the expedition."},{"time":822842,"text":"They're professionals,\nthey're speleologists and photographers."},{"time":825833,"text":"But when I look at these pictures,\nI wonder: there is zero light down there,"},{"time":830757,"text":"and yet they look incredibly well-exposed."},{"time":833564,"text":"How do you take these pictures?"},{"time":835076,"text":"How do your colleagues,\nthe photographers, take these pictures?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":838151,"text":"FS: Yeah. They are working\nin a darkroom, basically,"},{"time":840666,"text":"so you can open the shutter of the camera"},{"time":842809,"text":"and use the lights\nto paint the environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":845251,"text":"BG: So you're basically --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":846530,"text":"FS: Yes. You can even keep\nthe shutter open for one minute"},{"time":849289,"text":"and then paint the environment."},{"time":850837,"text":"The final result is what\nyou want to achieve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":853565,"text":"BG: You spray the environment with light\nand that's what you get."},{"time":856662,"text":"Maybe we can try this at home\nsomeday, I don't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":859128,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":860156,"text":"BG: Francesco, grazie.\nFS: Grazie."}]},{"cues":[{"time":861771,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}